abstract: His apology for the stop-and-frisk policy is politically convenient.
snippet: His apology for the stop-and-frisk policy is politically convenient.
lead_paragraph: Last Sunday I wrote a column entitled “You Must Never Vote for Bloomberg” because of Michael Bloomberg’s promotion, advocacy and defense of the racist stop-and-frisk policy that ballooned during his terms as mayor of New York City.

abstract: Prosecutors and police should honor the will of the voters and implement long-overdue changes.
snippet: Prosecutors and police should honor the will of the voters and implement long-overdue changes.
lead_paragraph: Across the country, a movement away from incarceration has been a rare point of consensus among Americans who can agree on little else.

headline_main: A Sad Last Gasp Against Criminal Justice Reform

abstract: Michael Bloomberg has apologized for overseeing an expansion of the controversial street-stop program as mayor.
snippet: Michael Bloomberg has apologized for overseeing an expansion of the controversial street-stop program as mayor.
lead_paragraph: During Michael R. Bloomberg’s tenure as mayor of New York City, police officers stopped and questioned people they believed to be engaged in criminal activity on the street more than five million times.

abstract: Money can’t buy the good will of a crucial Democratic constituency, black voters, ahead of a likely presidential bid.
snippet: Money can’t buy the good will of a crucial Democratic constituency, black voters, ahead of a likely presidential bid.
lead_paragraph: At a black church in New York on Sunday, Michael Bloomberg stood before the congregation and repented.

headline_main: Bloomberg Apologizes for Stop-and-Frisk at Just the Right Time
headline_print_headline: Mr. Bloomberg Apologizes at Just the Right Time

abstract: Ahead of a possible Democratic run for president, the former mayor of New York City reversed himself before an important party constituency: black voters.
snippet: Ahead of a possible Democratic run for president, the former mayor of New York City reversed himself before an important party constituency: black voters.
lead_paragraph: Ahead of a potential Democratic presidential run, former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg of New York on Sunday reversed his longstanding support of the aggressive “stop-and-frisk” policing strategy that he pursued for a decade and that led to the disproportionate stopping of black and Latino people across the city.

abstract: Mr. Buttigieg had a surprisingly robust lead in the latest Des Moines Register and CNN poll. Elizabeth Warren, Bernie Sanders and Joseph R. Biden Jr. were in a statistical tie for second.
snippet: Mr. Buttigieg had a surprisingly robust lead in the latest Des Moines Register and CNN poll. Elizabeth Warren, Bernie Sanders and Joseph R. Biden Jr. were in a statistical tie for second.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Pete Buttigieg continues to surge in Iowa, leapfrogging Senator Elizabeth Warren and former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to hold a commanding lead among likely Democratic caucusgoers, according to a new poll from The Des Moines Register and CNN.

abstract: A federal tax break intended to draw investment to lower-income areas has become one more way for the rich to avoid paying taxes.
snippet: A federal tax break intended to draw investment to lower-income areas has become one more way for the rich to avoid paying taxes.
lead_paragraph: Of all the ways President Trump’s 2017 tax cut has enriched the wealthy at the expense of the public interest, perhaps the most outrageous is the black comedy of “opportunity zones.”

abstract: Here are five things happened on the presidential campaign trail this week, as impeachment hearings began in Washington.
snippet: Here are five things happened on the presidential campaign trail this week, as impeachment hearings began in Washington.
lead_paragraph: There was more upheaval in the 2020 race this week, as one new Democratic candidate entered, another moved closer to doing so and a Republican dropped his primary challenge to President Trump. Here’s a look at the highlights.

abstract: Former President Barack Obama, in an address to liberal donors, warned candidates not to go too far left and sought to calm those who were concerned about the state of the Democratic primary.
snippet: Former President Barack Obama, in an address to liberal donors, warned candidates not to go too far left and sought to calm those who were concerned about the state of the Democratic primary.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Former President Barack Obama offered an unusual warning to the Democratic primary field on Friday evening, cautioning the candidates not to move too far to the left in their policy proposals, even as he sought to reassure a party establishment worried about the electoral strength of their historically large primary field.
